# n8n Dev/Stag Webhook Routing

## Invariant

When developing locally (`localhost:3000` → dev Supabase at `xxissfhcdjivuhxwjyhv`), the `N8N_*_WEBHOOK_URL`
env vars in `.env.local` **MUST** point at the `-STAG` workflow variant's UUID webhook path,
**NOT** the bare slug shared with the production workflow.

| Workflow family | Prod webhook path (DO NOT USE in dev)       | Stag webhook path (use in dev)                                            |
|-----------------|---------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| WF-VEP-001      | `/webhook/vep-001-extract`                  | `/webhook/f1d3e5ed-ee01-4a00-8201-0803228701c2` (WF-VEP-001-STAG)         |
| WF-VEP-002      | `/webhook/vep-002-social`                   | `/webhook/a40cb90d-ef00-407a-b3db-1b03e585cbb4` (WF-VEP-002-STAG)         |

> **WF-CLG-002 retired (2026-04-27):** Outreach drafts are now generated in-app
> via `generateOutreachDraftInApp` (`lib/outreach-queue-generator.ts`), so there
> is no `/webhook/clg-outreach-gen` to route in dev anymore. The auto-follow-up
> branch of WF-CLG-003 calls `/api/webhooks/n8n/outreach-followup-trigger`
> (Bearer `N8N_INGEST_SECRET`) directly on the deployed app.

Both are hosted at `https://amadutown.app.n8n.cloud`. The Supabase credential bound to the node
determines which DB is queried — prod paths use a prod cred, STAG paths use the dev cred.
Sending a `contact_id` that only exists in dev to a prod workflow produces a **silent** empty
`Get Lead Data` result; there is no error, and (historically) no failure callback either — the
graph simply ends at node 2/16 with `status: success`.

## Smell / symptoms (VEP family)

- VEP completion callback never reaches the app; `last_vep_status` stays `pending`
- n8n execution shows fewer nodes than expected; `Get Lead Data`-style fetches return 0 rows
- No POST hits the relevant `/api/webhooks/...` on the app server

## VEP-001 silent-failure hardening (same family of bug)

The VEP pipeline had a related but different silent-failure class: when `Prepare Text for
Classification` filtered all input items out (dev-only `contact_submission_id` not present in
prod DB, or ingest path simply returned 0 evidence items), the classifier received empty text,
the AI refused, the parser emitted `_empty: true`, and — in STAG — the graph **ended with no
callback at all** (no false-branch on `Filter Empty Results`). Eric's contact row sat at
`last_vep_status = 'pending'` for 15 days as a result.

As of 2026-04-24, both `WF-VEP-001` (`iqGylSD1c2lDxlDT`) and `WF-VEP-001-STAG`
(`7YdqfO7rewTHICHy`) have been hardened. The end-to-end contract is now:

1. **Every terminal callback echoes `contact_submission_ids`.** The app's
   `/api/admin/value-evidence/workflow-complete` uses those IDs to flip
   `contact_submissions.last_vep_status` from `pending` → `success` (or `failed`), regardless
   of how many evidence items were inserted. Previously this endpoint only touched
   `value_evidence_workflow_runs`, leaving leads stranded in `pending`.
2. **`Filter Empty Results` has both branches wired.** STAG now has a `Report Completion
   (No Items)` callback on the false branch (matching prod's long-standing node), so an
   empty-AI-result can no longer exit silently.
3. **Both workflows set `errorWorkflow` to self.** The `Error Trigger` → `Report Failure`
   pair is no longer dead code; any thrown error now emits a `failed` callback.
4. **Prod no longer hardcodes `N8N_INGEST_SECRET`.** All four HTTP callback nodes in prod
   (`POST to Ingest Endpoint`, `Report Completion`, `Report Failure`,
   `Report Completion (No Items)`) now pull `=Bearer {{ $vars.N8N_INGEST_SECRET }}` from n8n
   Variables, matching STAG. Rotating the secret only requires an n8n Variables update.
5. **App-side stale sweeper.** `lib/vep-contact-status.ts#partitionVepReconcile` (mirror of
   `partitionN8nOutreachReconcile`) runs on every `/api/admin/outreach/leads` GET and flips
   any `pending` row older than `STALE_VEP_PENDING_MS` (15 min) to `failed`. This is the
   belt-and-suspenders against any future callback-drop.

Do not remove any of these branches. If you edit the workflows, preserve the
`contact_submission_ids` echo in every terminal HTTP callback body — the shape the app
expects is documented at the top of `app/api/admin/value-evidence/workflow-complete/route.ts`.

